Tnode* add_tnode ( Tnode *  current_tnode,
char *  value 
)

Add a Tnode to a Tnode on left child if value is alphabetically before or equal or right child if alphabetically after.

Parameters:
current_tnode The node to attach the new node to.If NULL, will allocate a new Node and return it
value The value to place in the new node.
Returns:
Pointer to the Tnode or NULL if operation failed
